documentation.title: Chat Threads
documentation.description: Retrieve chat threads in the workspace.

documentation.title: Workspace
documentation.description: Identifier of a workspace, for example a Discord guild or a Slack workspace.

documentation.title: Threads
documentation.description: List of retrieved threads

documentation.title: Rate Limit
documentation.description: Rate limit details.

documentation.title: Get Threads
documentation.description: Retrieve list of threads from the whole workspace.

documentation.title: Id
documentation.description: Unique identifier of the thread

documentation.title: Created At
documentation.description: UNIX timestamp (in milliseconds, e.g. 1095379198750) when the thread was created

documentation.title: Channel
documentation.description: Unique identifier of the channel where the thread is located

documentation.title: Archive At
documentation.description:
UNIX timestamp (in milliseconds, e.g. 1095379198750) when the thread will be archived
Some providers limit the lifetime of threads and automatically archive them after some time period of inactivity.

documentation.title: Name
documentation.description: Name of retrieved thread

documentation.title: Members Count
documentation.description: Number of users participating in the thread

documentation.title: Messages Count
documentation.description: Number of messages in the retrieved thread

documentation.title: Last Message At
documentation.description: UNIX timestamp (in milliseconds, e.g. 1095379198750) when was the last message sent to thread.

documentation.title: Title
documentation.description: A short, human-readable summary of the problem type.

documentation.title: Detail
documentation.description: A human-readable explanation specific to this occurrence of the problem.

documentation.title: Rate Limit
documentation.description: Rate limit details.

documentation.title: Bucket
documentation.description:
Different parts of API may have different rate limits.
Bucket identifies to which part of API the rate limits apply.

documentation.title: Total Requests
documentation.description: Total requests available in the time window.

documentation.title: Remaining Requests
documentation.description: Remaining requests available in the time window.

documentation.title: Remaining Requests available in percents
documentation.description: Remaining requests available in the time window in percents.

documentation.title: Reset Timestamp
documentation.description: Timestamp when the rate limits will reset (in Unix Timestamp ms format).

documentation.title: Reset After
documentation.description: Number of seconds until reset of rate limit

documentation.title: Retry After
documentation.description: Number of seconds until user can retry the request
